    {
      "id": "decision:M009:1",
      "label": "**Repository pattern for all domain entities** — Using Repository classes (DealRepository, ContractRepository) with singleton exports provides clean separation between business logic and data access, making testing and future refactoring easier. Source: S01-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "decision:M009:2",
      "label": "**Auto-numbering schemes for business entities** — Deals use С-YYYY-NNNNN format, contracts use Д-YYYY-NNNNN. This provides user-friendly identifiers and makes cross-referencing easier than UUIDs alone. Source: S01-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "decision:M009:3",
      "label": "**Separate endpoint for state transitions** — POST /api/deals/[id]/move endpoint explicitly handles stage changes with DealHistory recording, rather than burying logic in generic PATCH. This makes the action explicit and auditable. Source: S01-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "decision:M009:4",
      "label": "**@dnd-kit for drag-and-drop** — Chose @dnd-kit/core over alternatives (react-beautiful-dnd, react-dnd) as the modern standard for React drag-and-drop with better accessibility and smaller bundle. Source: S02-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "decision:M009:5",
      "label": "**Separate tables for versioning and signers** — ContractVersion and ContractSigner as separate entities with one-to-many relationships provides better query flexibility and audit trails than embedding JSON in the contract record. Source: S04-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "decision:M009:6",
      "label": "**Dedicated convert endpoint for Deal→Contract** — POST /api/deals/[id]/convert makes the conversion action explicit and traceable, linking dealId to the new contract. Source: S04-SUMMARY.md/key_decisions",
      "type": "decision",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson:M009:1",
      "label": "**Post-validation integration gaps are common** — The Deal→Contract UI trigger was missing after initial validation (S05 only had API, not the button). A post-validation fix added the \"В контракт\" button to close the gap. Source: M009-VALIDATION.md/Cross-Slice Integration",
      "type": "lesson",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson:M009:2",
      "label": "**Timeline components should follow established patterns** — DealHistoryTimeline reused the InteractionTimeline pattern from M002 for consistency, demonstrating that early pattern establishment pays dividends across features. Source: S03-SUMMARY.md/Patterns Established",
      "type": "lesson",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "pattern:M009:1",
      "label": "**Repository pattern with singleton export** — Repository classes export a singleton instance rather than the class itself, simplifying import and usage patterns across the codebase. Source: S01-SUMMARY.md/patterns_established",
      "type": "pattern",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "pattern:M009:2",
      "label": "**API routes with standard CRUD structure** — GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/resource/[id] for single resources, GET/POST /api/resource for collections. Nested routes for sub-entities (versions, signers). Source: S01-SUMMARY.md/patterns_established",
      "type": "pattern",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "pattern:M009:3",
      "label": "**List + detail page structure** — /deals lists items with filters, /deals/[id] shows details. This pattern repeats across contacts, deals, and contracts for UX consistency. Source: S02-SUMMARY.md/patterns_established",
      "type": "pattern",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "pattern:M009:4",
      "label": "**Loading/error/empty state pattern for async UI** — All async components (KanbanBoard, DealHistoryTimeline, ContractsList) handle three states: loading spinner, error message with retry, empty state. Source: S03-SUMMARY.md/patterns_established",
      "type": "pattern",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "pattern:M009:5",
      "label": "**History data as optional array on data types** — DealData extends with optional history?: DealHistoryData[]. This keeps history data lightweight while maintaining type safety. Source: S03-SUMMARY.md/patterns_established",
      "type": "pattern",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    },
    {
      "id": "surprise:M009:1",
      "label": "**Task plan deviation in S05** — T01 was planned to create the /contracts page, but implementation created ContractRepository and contractsApi client first. The page was actually created in T03. Despite plan reordering, the slice delivered successfully. Source: S05-SUMMARY.md/Deviations",
      "type": "lesson",
      "confidence": "EXTRACTED",
      "sourceFile": "milestones/M009/M009-LEARNINGS.md"
    }
